ridge the gaps between action and contemplation, emotion and reason, and body and soul, offering new ways of thinking about language and the limits of representation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  amysticism, mystic, sex, sexual, sexuality, history, historical, religion, religious, 20th century, french, france, luce irigaray, jacques lacan, simone de beauvoir, georges bataille, psychology, psychological, philosophy, philosophical, psychoanalysis, trauma, catastrophe, feminism, gender, belief, communication, metaphysics, intellectuals, intellectualism, emotion, contemplation, teresa of avila, hadewijch, subjectivity, body.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022634951040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226349466423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226349466/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles